Description: An automated method to quantitatively identify and extract age plateaus
    from LA-ICP-MS depth profiling data of zircon U-Pb geochronology. The package
    implements ARIMA-based outlier detection, LOESS smoothing, PELT changepoint
    segmentation, multi-step plateau filtering (forward/reverse), Bayesian MCMC
    posterior analysis, and publication-ready visualization. Supports three input
    formats: direct U-Pb ages (Age68/Age75/Age76), raw isotope counts
    (Pb206/Pb207/U238), or isotopic ratios (Pb206_U238/Pb207_U235/Pb207_Pb206).
    Method described in Wang et al. (2026), JGR: Solid Earth, 131, e2025JB033324.
